<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-10"><hi rend="italic">October 10,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Apprehension of massacre of missionaries alike at Aleppo, Hadjin,
                            Mersine, and Marash. Missionaries here agree that danger would be
                            greater in transit than to stay calmly at their posts. * * * British
                            ambassador will apply for use of British vessels if needed to take
                            refuge before ours can arrive. British missions all located on the
                            coast. The situation here is still precarious. Orders have issued for
                            all provinces to protect Americans.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>